<plot>At what point do our own self-expectations become out of reach? That is the question that faces Derrick Mashburn. After being kicked off the college cross country team for accepting prize money at a local road race, Derrick is left with the choice to either pursue his education or rough it and follow his running. He has chosen the latter. Working as a house painter by day, Derrick trains when he can find the time, but quickly learns that success is not always measured by ribbons and medals.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?016786</url></doc>
